  "text": "IEEE Std 519-1992, \"IEEE Recommended Practices and Requirements for Harmonic Control in Power Systems,\" has become widely adopted in North America and is becoming more commonly applied globally as well. It sets limits for voltage and current distortion at a point of common coupling (PCC). It recognizes the responsibility of both user and utility in dealing with harmonic distortion. Interpretation of this standard is provided in [CITATION_1] .",
